// About Graph

What is Graph ?
 A graph can be defined as group of the vertices and Edges that are used to connect those vertices.

A graph is consist of two things 

1. A set V of element called node(or point or vertices).
2. A set E of edge such that each edges in E is unique pair of vertices.

// Termionology Used in the Graph
1. Adjacent Node 
2. Degree of Node
3. Isolated Node -> Node having degree is equal to zero
4. Path -> To reach from one vertex to another vertex the root followed is called path.
5. Cycle -> If we start traversing from one node and again we reached at same node is called cycle.
6. Loop -> If the edge has both same vertex is called loop
7. Parallel edge -> End or Start is same is called parallel edge and also have more than one edge.
